<div style="border: 2px solid black; background-color: Moccasin;">
<p style="text-align: center;">The dynamic nature of this wiki means that linked pages might get moved, renamed, deleted, or replaced. Old news pages remain as time capsules and are not updated to account for these changes.</p>
</div>



<p><span style="font-size:75%;">This is a series showing off news from the site, articles from the past month<sup class="footnoteref"><a id="footnoteref-1" href="javascript:;" class="footnoteref" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnote-1')">1</a></sup>, and fan-content for you to check out and discover! Be sure to leave a comment with your thoughts!</span></p>
<h4><span>Fandom Stuff</span></h4>
<ul>
<li>Check out this year's <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/t-12808111/8th-annual-holiday-art-exchange">8th Annual Holiday Art Exchange</a>! A merry time for all involved! If you weren't able to get in on this year's, mark your calendar for 2020!</li>
</ul>
<h4><span>Featured Articles</span></h4>
<ul>
<li><a href="/scp-3636">SCP-3636</a> - (&quot;World's Greatest Jukebox&quot;) - <em>The jukebox was found undamaged with the screen showing a video of the fire from the bar's exterior while playing the song &quot;We Didn't Start the Fire&quot; by Billy Joel.</em> By GerrymanderBassist</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><a href="/letters-to-my-future-self">letters to my future self</a> - <em>On 2014/04/30, a series of notes written on paper scraps were recovered from PoI-████'s temporary holding cell.</em> By AthosNetwork</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><a href="/spc-2922">SPC-2922</a> - <em>ITEETH-FILLED VOID is a desert within Corbenic that is perpetually night.</em> By Stormbreath.</li>
</ul>
<h4><span>Reviewer's Spotlight Articles</span></h4>
<ul>
<li><a href="/scp-4361">SCP-4361</a> - (&quot;Red is Her Favorite Color&quot;) - <em>Hurts to talk. Please. Hard to tal— (video ends)</em> Written by Kybard, selected by <em>Kybard.</em></li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><a href="/scp-4204">SCP-4204</a> - (&quot;To Pluck the Moon From the Sky&quot;) - <em>SCP-4204 was discovered when a person attempting to break into Fort Knox failed to exit the vault before sunrise.</em> Written by Dyslexion, selected by <em>PrLosash.</em></li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><a href="/scp-4428">Dr. Michaels</a> - (&quot;Dr. Michaels is not in danger.&quot;) - <em>DOMC NOTICE: This file requires non-anomalous comprehensive inoculation.</em> Written by Lt Flops and Henzoid, selected by <em>Vincent Van Gone.</em></li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><a href="/scp-4608">SCP-4608</a> - (&quot;Appleseed&quot;) - <em>Engraved on approximately 75% of trees within SCP-4608 were thaumaturgic sigils and symbols relating to Norse mythology.</em> Written by DrAkimoto, selected by <em>Dyslexion.</em></li>
</ul>
